The subject gives an overview of the use of sound equipment used  in music studios.  Technical base needed for sound recording  is introduced and the practical tasks are given (recording of acoustic instruments, different microphone techniques, live-performance management, mixing).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Aims of the subject:
* explaining the work and application principles of the equipment and recording devices in a modern recording studio, acquiring major working methods. 
* to provide student with basic knowledge and skills to independently use  recording studio possibilities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student
By the end of the course student:
* knows a basic structure of recording studio;
* is acquainted with recording studio equipment and software and principles of work of it;
* can use recording studio equipment in different steps of recording process.
